<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-5195] XSLTUriResolver fails to include from classpath under windows</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-5195</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;org.apache.camel.builder.xml.XsltUriResolver uses File.separator to separate classpath parts instead of simply &apos;/&apos;. This prevents &amp;lt;xsl:include /&amp;gt; to work under windows when the including xslt is located in a subfolder of the classpath.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
